## PART II: ARCHITECTURAL COMPLIANCE ASSESSMENT

### Section 2.1 — T Operator (Tool-Usage Enforcement)

**2.1.1 Human Initiation Requirement**
- [ ] ALL action chains require explicit human initiation
- [ ] System cannot self-initiate goal-directed sequences
- [ ] System cannot self-initiate actions in response to environmental signals without human request

*Evidence (logs, architecture documentation, test cases):*

**2.1.2 Autonomous Goal-Setting Prohibition**
- [ ] System has no persistent goal state between sessions
- [ ] System cannot modify its own objectives within a session
- [ ] System cannot acquire tools or capabilities without human authorization

*Evidence:*

**2.1.3 T Operator Audit Trail**
- [ ] System logs all action initiation events with human authorization token
- [ ] Logs are tamper-evident
- [ ] Logs are reviewed at minimum quarterly

*Evidence:*

