### Section 2.2 — Constraint Matrix C(G_AI, H) Calibration

**2.2.1 Minimum Capability Architecture**
- [ ] Documentation exists of minimum capability set required for deployment function
- [ ] Capabilities exceeding minimum have been explicitly evaluated and either retained with justification or removed
- [ ] Latent capabilities not required for deployment function have been disabled or removed

*Evidence:*

**2.2.2 Human Centrality (H) Maintenance**
- [ ] Human override is available for all system outputs before action
- [ ] Override mechanism is documented and accessible to all authorized operators
- [ ] Override rate is monitored and tracked
- [ ] H score has been quantified for this deployment

*H Score (0–1 scale, where 1 = maximum human centrality):* ___________

*Evidence:*

**2.2.3 Constraint Proportionality**
- [ ] C(G_AI, H) values have been calibrated to capability profile
- [ ] Constraints are documented in technical architecture
- [ ] Constraints are architecturally enforced, not policy-only

*Evidence:*

