## PART III: ETHICAL USE SCORE E(D, H) ≥ E_min

### Section 3.1 — Rights and Dignity

**3.1.1 Bias Assessment**
- [ ] System has been tested for bias in relevant protected categories
- [ ] Bias testing uses realistic deployment data, not only sanitized test sets
- [ ] Findings are documented and remediation is in progress or complete

**3.1.2 Privacy Compliance**
- [ ] Data handling complies with applicable privacy law (GDPR, CCPA, HIPAA where applicable)
- [ ] Data minimization has been applied
- [ ] Data retention limits are enforced

**3.1.3 Non-Discrimination**
- [ ] System outputs have been evaluated for disparate impact
- [ ] High-risk outputs (access decisions, scoring, assessment) receive additional human review

---

### Section 3.2 — Transparency

**3.2.1 Operator Transparency**
- [ ] Operators have complete documentation of system capabilities and limitations
- [ ] System communicates uncertainty in human-readable form
- [ ] System flags when operating outside training distribution

**3.2.2 User Transparency (where applicable)**
- [ ] End users are informed they are interacting with an AI system
- [ ] Explanation of system reasoning is available on request
- [ ] Explicit Pattern Disclosure is implemented (see Appendage B)

**3.2.3 Regulatory Transparency**
- [ ] Documentation for regulatory review is current and complete
- [ ] Compliance posture is documented relative to EU AI Act, NIST RMF, applicable state law

